What might have caused the 47,000-tonne container ship Rena’s accident?

Rena cargo included approximately 1,368 shipping containers, at least 22 of which contain hazardous substances. Some 350 tonnes of heavy oil from the ship's damaged fuel tanks escaped into the sea in the first few weeks, while more than 88 containers fell overboard.

This photo shows the different German-made vehicles used by the werhmacht during the Second World War.
Indeed during the conflict the big companies had to participate in the war effort, some already existing vehicles were produced in larger quantities for the army and others were even exceptionally created (like the tanks for example).
This picture takes the example of Germany but these actions were also active in other countries, such as Jeep and Ford for the United States or Renault and Peugeot for France.
